SIMPLE: speculator
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Speculator
<hw>Spec"u*la`tor</hw> <pr>(sp⟦ecr⟧k"⟦usl⟧*l⟦amac⟧`t⟦etil⟧r)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., a spy, explorer, investigator: cf. F.
<ets>sp⟦eacute⟧culateur</ets>.]</ety> <def>One who speculates.
Specifically: <sd>(a)</sd> An observer; a contemplator; hence, a spy; a
watcher.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Sir T. Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sd>(b)</sd> <def>One who forms theories; a theorist.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A <qex>speculator</qex> who had dared to affirm that the human
soul is by nature mortal.</q> <rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sd>(c)</sd> <fld>(Com.)</fld> <def>One who engages in speculation;
one who buys and sells goods, land, etc., with the expectation of
deriving profit from fluctuations in price.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1382 --></p>

<p><ent>Speculatorial</ent>⟦br⟧
